# Clean Architecture & MVVM — LLM Rules

When editing or generating code in this project, follow these rules. Inner layers MUST NOT depend on outer layers.

---

## Layer boundaries

**MUST**
- Put domain entities (interfaces only, e.g. `IPost`), use cases, and repository *interfaces* in `src/app/domain/`.
- Put raw API types and request params (DTOs) in `src/app/interfaces/dtos/`.
- Put adapters (raw → domain) in `src/app/interfaces/adapters/`.
- Put API implementations in `src/app/infrastructure/` and have them use adapters before returning to callers.
- Put server-side data fetching in `src/app/data/<feature>/` with `"use server"`, `"use cache"`, and `cacheTag()`.
- Put feature UI (components, hooks, optional models) in `src/app/ui/features/<feature>/` and shared UI in `src/app/ui/shared/`.
- Put DI bindings and API client config in `src/app/core/`.

**MUST NOT**
- Import from outer layers into domain (no `@/app/interfaces`, `@/app/infrastructure`, `@/app/data`, `@/app/ui`, `@/app/core` inside `domain/`).
- Use raw API types (e.g. `IRawPost`) or HTTP details in the domain layer; domain must stay independent of API contracts.
- Put server data fetching outside `data/` (e.g. do not fetch in page components directly from infrastructure or use cases).
- Define domain entities as classes or as `type` aliases; use `interface` only.

---

## Naming

**MUST**
- Name domain entity interfaces with `I` prefix: `IPost`, `IUser`.
- Name other interfaces (repositories, DTOs, services) with `I` prefix: `IPostsRepository`, `IRawPost`, `IGetPostParams`.
- Name use case classes with `U` prefix and give each a static `symbol`: e.g. `UGetAllPostsUseCase` with `static readonly symbol = Symbol.for("GetAllPostsUseCase")`.
- Resolve use cases by symbol in the data layer: `sl.get<UGetAllPostsUseCase>(UGetAllPostsUseCase.symbol)` — do not use hardcoded string tokens for use cases.
- Name enums with `E` prefix: `EPostType`, `EUserRole`.

**MUST NOT**
- Use `T` prefix for domain entities (no `TPost`); domain entities are interfaces with `I` prefix.
- Use hardcoded strings to resolve use cases from the container; always use the use case’s `symbol`.

---

## Dependency injection

**MUST**
- Mark use case classes with `@injectable()` and inject the repository with `@inject("Token")` (e.g. `@inject("PostsRepository")`).
- Mark repository implementation classes with `@injectable()`.
- Register bindings in `src/app/core/bindings/` and use the same token string in `@inject()` and in `sl.bind<...>("Token")`.

**MUST NOT**
- Resolve use cases in the UI layer; resolve them only in the data layer (server-side).

---

## Data flow and adapters

**MUST**
- Define raw API response and request shapes in `interfaces/dtos/` (e.g. `IRawPost`, `IGetPostParams`).
- Implement one or more adapter functions in `interfaces/adapters/<feature>/` that map raw DTOs to domain interfaces.
- In infrastructure (e.g. repository implementations), call the adapter on API responses before returning; return only domain interfaces (e.g. `IPost[]`), never raw DTOs to domain or data layer.
- Use `cacheTag()` in data services for invalidation (e.g. `cacheTag("posts")`, `cacheTag(\`post-${id}\`)`).

**MUST NOT**
- Return raw API types from infrastructure to the data layer or domain; always convert via adapters first.
- Put adapter logic inside the domain or infrastructure; keep adapters in `interfaces/adapters/`.

---

## MVVM and UI

**MUST**
- Keep React views presentational: receive data and callbacks as props, no direct use case or repository access.
- Use data layer services (server) and hooks in `ui/features/<feature>/hooks/` (client) as the bridge between domain and UI when working with domain entities.
- Put UI-only models (structures that do not map to domain entities) in `ui/features/<feature>/models/` or `view-models/` if needed.

**SHOULD NOT**
- Mirror domain entities in the UI layer unless the UI actually needs the same shape; prefer domain entities in hooks and props when the UI displays domain data.
- Put business logic in components; keep it in use cases or in ViewModels (data services / hooks).

---

## File and folder structure

**MUST**
- Organize by feature across layers: e.g. `domain/posts/`, `interfaces/dtos/posts/`, `interfaces/adapters/posts/`, `infrastructure/api/posts/`, `data/posts/`, `ui/features/posts/`.
- Place shared shadcn components under `ui/shared/components/ui/` and shared lib under `ui/shared/lib/`.
- Have pages and routes consume data via functions from `data/<feature>/`, not by importing use cases or infrastructure.

**SHOULD**
- Use `"use cache"` at the page level when a page primarily displays data from a cached data service.
- Use the same feature name (e.g. `posts`) in each layer for the same bounded context.

---

## Verification checklist (before submitting)

When adding or changing code, confirm:

- [ ] Domain has no imports from interfaces, infrastructure, data, ui, or core.
- [ ] Domain entities are `interface` with `I` prefix; use cases are classes with `U` prefix and `symbol`.
- [ ] Use cases use `@injectable()` and `@inject("...")`; repository impls use `@injectable()`.
- [ ] Use cases are resolved by `UseCase.symbol` in the data layer only.
- [ ] Raw types live in `interfaces/dtos/`; adapters in `interfaces/adapters/`; infrastructure uses adapters and returns domain types.
- [ ] Server data fetching lives in `data/<feature>/` with `"use server"`, `"use cache"`, and `cacheTag()`.
- [ ] Views do not call use cases or repositories directly; they use data services or hooks.
